CTF Write-Up — 1810 London Hoax Confession
Challenge

Decades after the 1810 London hoax, the culprit confessed inside his semi-autobiographical novel.
SECE{novel_name}

Step 1 — Isolate the historical event (OSINT pivot)

Key terms from the prompt:

1810

London

hoax

later confession

novel

Search logic:

1810 London hoax confession novel

This consistently points to the Berners Street Hoax, a famous mass prank involving hundreds of tradesmen being summoned to a single address.

Step 2 — Identify the culprit

Historical records attribute the hoax to:

Theodore Hook

A British writer known for elaborate practical jokes.

Step 3 — Locate the confession source

Further research on Hook reveals that he later admitted to orchestrating the hoax in his semi-autobiographical novel:

Gilbert Gurney

The novel includes a fictionalized but clear acknowledgment of the prank.

Step 4 — Format the flag

CTF convention replaces spaces with underscores:

SECE{gilbert_gurney}
Final Answer
SECE{gilbert_gurney}
